The paper deals with a data structure for the selection problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a new data structure that handles a dynamic version of the problem, which involves insertions and deletions of elements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves quantile groups, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper proposes a new design that slows down a certain computation to reduce response time, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AL (Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves ideal constant time operations, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves a new data structure, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
